org.postgresql.pljava.sqlgen

Class DDRProcessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.annotation.processing.AbstractProcessor
      • org.postgresql.pljava.sqlgen.DDRProcessor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Processor

    @SupportedAnnotationTypes(value="org.postgresql.pljava.annotation.*")
@SupportedOptions(value={"ddr.name.trusted","ddr.name.untrusted","ddr.implementor","ddr.output"})
@SupportedSourceVersion(value=RELEASE_6)
public class DDRProcessor
extends AbstractProcessor
    Annotation processor invoked by the annotations framework in javac for annotations of type org.postgresql.pljava.annotation.*. Simply forwards to a DDRProcessorImpl instance that is not constructed until the framework calls init (since there is nothing useful for the constructor to do until then).
    Author:
    Thomas Hallgren - pre-Java6 version, Chapman Flack (Purdue Mathematics) - update to Java6, add SQLType/SQLAction, polishing
